<p>The weight loss peptide space changed when <a href="/articles/tirzepatide-complete-guide">tirzepatide</a> proved that targeting two incretin receptors at once could outperform single-agonist drugs like <a href="/articles/semaglutide-weight-loss-guide">semaglutide</a>. Now <a href="/articles/retatrutide-complete-guide">retatrutide</a> is pushing that logic one step further by adding a third receptor to the mix.</p>

<p>These are not interchangeable medications. They work through different receptor combinations, produce different metabolic effects, and sit at very different points in the regulatory timeline. This comparison breaks down what actually matters when evaluating them.</p>

